# Architecture Principles

## Module boundaries (enforce strictly)

```
src/
  app/          # Streamlit entry + pages. Wiring only. No LLM calls.
  core/         # Types, settings, constants, exceptions. No deps on llm/judges.
  ingestion/    # Load, map, validate, normalize. Single source of truth for
                # source schemas.
  llm/          # Provider layer. ONLY place vendor SDKs live.
  judges/       # One module per pillar. No provider SDK imports, no Streamlit.
  rubrics/      # Rubric loader + models. Versioned.
  completeness/ # Completeness KB loader, matcher, task profile builder.
  evaluation/   # Metrics, agreement, slices, stability, reviewer analysis.
  orchestration/# Run a judge across a dataset. Concurrency, batching, caching.
  observability/# MLflow + Langfuse + run metadata fingerprints.
  dashboard/    # Reusable charts, tables, filters. Read-only on results.
  exports/      # Writers and reports.
configs/        # models / judges / rubrics / mappings / runs / knowledge.
tests/          # unit, integration, fixtures.
```

## Non-negotiable rules

1. **LLM provider isolation.** Vendor SDKs (`openai`, `anthropic`,
   `google-*`) import ONLY in `src/llm/*_client.py`. Judges, UI, metrics,
   and dashboards call the `LLMClient` interface.
2. **Config-driven judges and rubrics.** Rubric version, prompt version,
   model alias, temperature, retry policy come from `configs/judges/<pillar>.yaml`
   and `configs/rubrics/<pillar>.yaml`. No magic constants in code.
3. **Normalized schema.** Downstream code operates on `NormalizedRow`
   (`src/core/types.py`). Ingestion is the only place that knows source schemas.
4. **Strict structured outputs.** Every judge returns a Pydantic-validated
   `JudgeResult` (see `docs/JUDGE_OUTPUT_CONTRACT.md`). Parse failures retry
   then tag `parse_failed`, never silently drop.
5. **Reproducibility.** Every run records: `run_id`, `dataset_fingerprint`,
   `rubric_version`, `prompt_version`, `model_alias`/`model_version`,
   `kb_version`, `run_config_hash`.
6. **No cross-imports from `app/` or `dashboard/` into `llm/` or judge
   internals.** They go through `orchestration/` and `evaluation/`.

## Dependency direction

`app → orchestration → {judges, evaluation, ingestion, exports}
                        ↓         ↓         ↓         ↓
                     core ← llm, rubrics, completeness, observability
dashboard → evaluation, core`

Never import upward.
